===Etymology===
From {{proto|Indo-European|táwros|lang=la}}. Cognates include Ancient Greek {{term|ταῦρος||tr=tauros|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, Old Prussian {{term|tauris|lang=prg}} and Old English {{term|steor|stēor|lang=ang}} (English {{term|steer|lang=en}}).{{rfv-etymology}} Possibly of Semitic origin; confer {{proto|Semitic|θawr-|title=Common Semitic|lang=}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|Classical}} {{IPA|/ˈtau.rus/|lang=la}}
* {{audio|la-cls-taurus.ogg|Audio (Classical)}}

===Noun===
{{la-noun|taurus|tauri|taurī|m|second}}

# a [[bull]], [[steer]]
# an instrument of [[torture]], in the shape of a bull
# a small [[bird]] that sounds like the [[lowing]] of [[ox]]en, possibly the [[bittern]]
# a kind of [[beetle]]
# {{anatomy|lang=la}} the [[perineum]]

